        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") in words and deeds. [",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "It is by the undaunted confession of Christ itself that His own life is brought into danger",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ".—V. g.]—",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "Με",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "—",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "ὁ Υἱὸς τοῦ ἀνθρώπου",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Me—the Son of Man",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") concerning the present time, He speaks in the first person [",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Me",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "]; concerning the future, in the third [",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "the Son of Man",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "λόγους",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "words",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") of the cross [which carry with them the need of taking up a cross). The plural implies, that one may confess Christ in general, and yet be ashamed of this or that word, this or that saying of His; for instance, Matthew 5 This kind of shame must also be overcome.—",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "ἐν τῇ γενεᾷ ταύτῃ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "in this generation",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") To this there stands in antithesis the general assembly of the last day, which is spoken of presently after.—",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "τῇ μοιχαλίδι καὶ ἁμαρτωλῷ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "this adulterous and sinful",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") which, as ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "an adulteress",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", despises ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Christ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ":[2] as ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "sinful",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", despises ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "His words",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ": and in consequence throws out in the way of those who confess Him all kinds of threats and promises. Such a crowd ought to be altogether despised. Who need fear them?—who regard them?—",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "ὁ Υἱὸς ἀνθρώπου",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "the Son of Man",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") He had just now said, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Me and My words",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", not ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "the Son of Man and His words",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; but now He does not say, I, but the ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Song of Solomon of Man",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", which appellation has a peculiar connection with His glorious and visible Advent. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Luke 9:26",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ".—",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "ἐπαισχυνθήσεται",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "shall regard as an object of shame",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") with good reason: and so shall not acknowledge as His, but shall put away from Him.—",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "τοῦ Πατρὸς",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "the Father",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") Therefore His glory is, as of the Only-begotten of the Father, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "John 1:14",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ".—",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "μετὰ τῶν ἀγγέλων τῶν ἁγίων",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") This is the ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Greek",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " reading, and that of the ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Goth",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". Version, etc. See App. Crit. Ed. ii. on this passage. O what shame! To be regarded as an object of shame in the presence of God the Father, of Christ, and of angels!",
        "children": []
      },
      {
