  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Pulpit Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_sub_title",
        "text": "Verse 38.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " - Our Lord here looks onward to the day of judgment. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "Whosoever shall be ashamed of me",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". \"Whosoever:\" the word includes all, whatever their position or circumstances may be. \"Shall be ashamed of me;\" that is, shall deny my faith, or blush to confess me here. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "Of him shall the Son of man be ashamed",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; that is, Christ will despise him, when he shall appear with power and great glory, in that sublime majesty which he gained by his death upon the cross. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "In this adulterous and sinful",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "generation.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " It adds to the disgrace of being ashamed of Christ that the shame is manifested in the presence of the base and the worthless; and therefore our Lord exhibits the contrast between the mean and contemptible people in the presence of whom men are ashamed of him here, and the magnificent assemblage in whose presence he will be ashamed of them hereafter. The cross of Christ appeared to the great body of mankind to be shameful and contemptible. To the Jews it was a stumbling-block, and to the Greek's foolishness. Hence vast numbers, whether through shame or fear, did not dare to confess it, and still less to preach it. And therefore it is that St. Paul says (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Romans 1",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ":l6), \"I am not ashamed of the gospel of Christ.\" ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " Mark 8:38",
        "children": []
      },
